  "text": "Following the discussion at the beginning of Appendix A.2 (p. 30) in [CITATION_1] , we can assume without loss of generality that the drift b t is null. Furthermore, following the proof in the jump case in Appendix A.6 (p. 40), it is clear that the following proof adapts straightforwardly to the jump case, and then we assume without loss of generality that X t is continuous in what follows.",
